char firstNonRepeating(char* str) {
    int freq[256] = {0};
    int len = strlen(str);
    // Count frequencies
    for (int i = 0; i < len; i++)
        freq[(unsigned char)str[i]]++;
    // Find first char with frequency 1
    for (int i = 0; i < len; i++)
        if (freq[(unsigned char)str[i]] == 1)
            return str[i];
    return '\0'; // no non-repeating char
}
```
Use a frequency array of size 256 (ASCII). First pass counts frequencies, second pass finds the first character with count 1. Time: O(n), Space: O(1) since array size is constant.

