            second = arr[i];
        }
    }
    return second; // returns -1 if no second largest
}
```
Single pass maintaining first and second largest. Time: O(n), Space: O(1). Skip duplicates of the largest.

```c
void moveZeros(int arr[], int n) {
    int writeIdx = 0;
    // Move all non-zero elements forward
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (arr[i] != 0) {
            arr[writeIdx++] = arr[i];
        }
    }
    // Fill remaining positions with zeros
    while (writeIdx < n) {
        arr[writeIdx++] = 0;
    }
}
```
Use a write pointer. First pass copies non-zeros to front, second pass fills rest with zeros. Time: O(n), Space: O(1). Maintains relative order of non-zero elements.

