int fibonacci(int n) {
    if (n <= 1) return n;
    int dp[n + 1];
    dp[0] = 0;
    dp[1] = 1;
    for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
        dp[i] = dp[i-1] + dp[i-2];
    }
    return dp[n];
}
// Space-optimized version:
int fibOptimized(int n) {
    if (n <= 1) return n;
    int prev2 = 0, prev1 = 1, curr;
    for (int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
        curr = prev1 + prev2;
        prev2 = prev1;
        prev1 = curr;
    }
    return prev1;
}
```
Tabulation builds answer iteratively from base cases. Time: O(n), Space: O(n) for array version, O(1) for optimized version. Much better than recursive O(2^n).

Use the Dutch National Flag algorithm with three pointers — low (boundary of 0s), mid (current element), high (boundary of 2s) — and swap in a single O(n) pass with O(1) space:
```
void sort012(int[] a) {
  int low = 0, mid = 0, high = a.length - 1;
  while (mid <= high) {
    if (a[mid] == 0) { swap(a, low++, mid++); }
    else if (a[mid] == 1) { mid++; }
    else { swap(a, mid, high--); }   // a[mid]==2, don't advance mid
  }
}
```
Key idea: when you swap a 2 to the back you do NOT advance mid, because the element swapped in is still unexamined. Time O(n), space O(1).

Maintain a min-heap of size k. Push elements; once the heap exceeds k, pop the smallest. The heap's root is then the k-th largest. Time O(n log k), space O(k):
```
int kthLargest(int[] nums, int k) {
  PriorityQueue<Integer> minHeap = new PriorityQueue<>();
  for (int x : nums) {
    minHeap.offer(x);
    if (minHeap.size() > k) minHeap.poll();
  }
  return minHeap.peek();
}
```
Alternative: Quickselect (partition around a pivot like quicksort, recurse only into the side containing index n-k) gives average O(n) time, worst case O(n^2). Sorting first is the simplest at O(n log n).

Use a sliding window with two pointers and a frequency map of the characters needed from t. Expand the right pointer to satisfy the window, then contract the left pointer to shrink it while still valid, tracking the smallest valid window:
```
String minWindow(String s, String t) {
  if (t.isEmpty()) return "";
  int[] need = new int[128];
  for (char c : t.toCharArray()) need[c]++;
  int required = t.length(), left = 0, bestLen = Integer.MAX_VALUE, bestL = 0;
  for (int right = 0; right < s.length(); right++) {
    if (need[s.charAt(right)]-- > 0) required--;
    while (required == 0) {                       // window is valid
      if (right - left + 1 < bestLen) { bestLen = right - left + 1; bestL = left; }
      if (need[s.charAt(left)]++ == 0) required++; // about to break validity
      left++;
    }
  }
  return bestLen == Integer.MAX_VALUE ? "" : s.substring(bestL, bestL + bestLen);
}
```
Time O(|s| + |t|), space O(1) for a fixed alphabet.
